<div id="wiki-tab-0-5" style="display:none">
<p>SAPPHIRE seems to maintain numerous antagonistic relations among the anomalous world and the other groups of interest, which does not minimize its threat but insures to &quot;keep them busy&quot;. Those antagonisms include notably:</p>
<h2 id="toc0"><span>The Office for the Reclamation of Islamic Artifacts:</span></h2>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> Defensive / Active</p>
<p>Although the information about it is vague, it seems that several SAPPHIRE-related attacks had already happened in Middle-East during the last century, in spite of the geographical remoteness of the target from the European core of the Society. However, since the implementation of the ORIA in the eighties, the atheist attacks seems to be easily controlled, and tens of the members of the Society had been caught/executed by the Islamic forces over the past thirty years.</p>
<p>ORIA’s position about SAPPHIRE is unknown, but the measures taken appear to be effective.</p>
<h2 id="toc1"><span>The Global Occult Coalition:</span></h2>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> Offensive / Active</p>
<p>The GOC's archives show that SAPPHIRE was previously part of the Council of 108 during the formation of the Coalition, but the Atheist Society left its seat as soon as 1953 following <a class="newpage" href="/partager-le-vin">ideological divergences</a>, as the Coalition started protecting civilian religions and recruiting numerous consultant thaumaturges.</p>
<p>SAPPHIRE is today under an Alpha class arrest warrant from the GOC because of the threat it is against the organization and the civilian world since its departure.</p>
<h2 id="toc2"><span>The Humanist Gentlemen:</span></h2>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> Competitive / Active</p>
<p>The historical data seems to indicate that SAPPHIRE and the Gentlemen have their sources in the same organization which, during the 18<sup>th</sup> century, fought for the emancipation of Man in the anomalous world. However, a split occurred between the Gentlemen, who were trying to use the SCP objects and make them work for their values, and SAPPHIRE, who felt that Humanity should, before anything else, free itself from irrationality by the destruction of these objects.</p>
<p>SAPPHIRE and the Gentlemen appear to show a mutual &quot;respectful hate&quot;, conscious of their shared origin and ideology but convinced that the other camp is wrong. However, they seem to avoid direct conflict.</p>
<h2 id="toc3"><span>The Horizon Initiative:</span></h2>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> Defensive / Semi-inactive</p>
<p>The alliance of the three biggest Abrahamic religions dedicated to the management of SCP objects is, of course, the first target of SAPPHIRE, and the only one being able to respond to the attacks from the Society since neither the Vatican, nor the Mecca, nor Israel can publicly adjudicate on the field of the anomalous.</p>
<p>A sub-ministry was recently created within the Malleus Project to face up to the threat of the anomalous extremist atheism but seems to restrict itself to defensive measure and has very little organization.</p>
<h2 id="toc4"><span>The Mossad:</span></h2>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> Defensive / Active</p>
<p>Due to the religious center that Israel and more specifically Jerusalem embodies, it appears that SAPPHIRE took advantage of the local geopolitical tensions to orchestrate several attacks undercover, in particular at the end of the nineties. Although most of those attacks were foiled, the Israeli government is warned about the existence of SAPPHIRE, and a national plan of securing against extremist atheism was set up secretly under the responsibility of the Mossad and in collaboration with the Shabak.</p>
<p>Although the nature of this plan is unknown, no attack from SAPPHIRE appears to have occurred on the Israeli territory since 1998.</p>
<h2 id="toc5"><span>The Anomalous Religions:</span></h2>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> Unknown / Unknown</p>
<p>Although we know that SAPPHIRE targets essentially anomalous cults and Groups of Interest of religious nature, there is little leaked information about possible attacks (successful or not) against them. These occult religions most often manage these cases internally and let little information leak from their underworld.</p>
<p>These groups include but are not limited to: the Sarkic cults, the Church of the Broken God, the Fifth Church, the Order of the Light, and smaller sects such as the Sons of Seth (GOI-0236) or the Holy Proscribed Company (GOI-0092).</p>
<p>Through retrieved documents, it’s known that SAPPHIRE has undercover agents within the Fifth Church and the Order of the Light, at low-rank position. It appears unlikely that they would have some within the Church of the Broken God or Sarkic groups since those currents call their members to perform anomalous modifications to their bodies (bionic implants, diseases propagation, etc.).</p>
<h2 id="toc6"><span>The Vatican:</span></h2>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> Defensive / Inactive</p>
<p>The Holy See has been officially warned about the threat they were exposed to by the Horizon Initiative in 1979 following the events of the Trevi Fountain. Since this day, it has come to the notice of the Foundation that a secret document called <em>&quot;The Pious Letter in front of the Incredulous&quot;</em> is passed on from pope to pope. The exact nature of this document is unknown, though it’s supposed to be a protocol dictating how the Church should react and organize should God die.</p>
